                  "BodyCopy": "\u003cp\u003eThe Silk Road ran through here on its perilous but popular path from China to Europe, bringing both trade and foreign influence. The region\u0026rsquo;s nomadic tribes frequently mixed with those from across East, North-east and Central Asia, and empires \u0026ndash; from Genghis Khan\u0026rsquo;s Mongols up to the Soviet Union \u0026ndash; have often taken over. (Credit: Amanda Ruggeri)\u003c/p\u003e",
