            "BodyCopy": "\u003cp\u003eAs late as the 1950s and 1960s, there was a blaa bakery boom in Waterford, with about 15 bakeries making blaas in the city at the time. Today, there are only a couple in Waterford proper. (Two others in the \u003ca href=\"http://waterfordblaa.ie/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eWaterford Blaa Bakers Association\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://www.barronsbakery.ie/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBarron\u0026rsquo;s\u003c/a\u003e and Kilmacow, are outside the city).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne is Hickey\u0026rsquo;s, which opened in 1958 and is now run by the third generation of the Hickey family. \u0026ldquo;Small bakeries now are very few and far between,\u0026rdquo; said Hickey, who chalks the change up to the industrialisation of Irish food and growth of big factories. \u0026ldquo;Put it this way: if the blaas weren\u0026rsquo;t here, there\u0026rsquo;d be no bakeries in Waterford. The blaas are what\u0026rsquo;s keeping us open.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e",
